# `pi-e` and playground link modes

When changing **`just pi-e`**, **`scripts/pi-launch-from-project.sh`**, **`init-project-local-pi-env.sh`**, **`enable-playground-in-project`**, **`render-project-wired-playground-settings.py`**, **`link-playground-agent-trees.sh`**, or user-facing text about **`ppi pi-e`** / **`PIE_*`**:

**`HAD_MENU_EXTENSION`** = selection includes **`all`**, any **menu number ≥ 3**, or a **label** that resolves to a real **`.ts`** (not pseudo **`__...__`**).

| Situation | `PIE_CLEAR_SETTINGS_EXTENSIONS` (unless **`PIE_KEEP_SETTINGS_EXTENSIONS=1`**) |
|-----------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| **Option 1 only** or **`1` + `2` only** (no menu line 3+) | **0** — Pi loads full **`extensions[]`** from **`.pi/settings.json`**. |
| **Option `2` only** (no line 3+) | **1** — wired JSON already has **`extensions": []`**; same clear path. |
| **Any menu extension (3+)** or **`all`**, **with or without** 1/2 | **1** — only stacked **`-e`** for this run (e.g. **`1 12`** → **agent-team** only, not the whole merged list). |

- Avoid **`if ! $PLAYGROUND_FULL_ENABLE`** when the var is **`0`/`1`** — use **`[[ "$PLAYGROUND_FULL_ENABLE" == "1" ]]`** (otherwise bash tries to run command **`1`**).
- **Canonical doc:** **[docs/PLAYGROUND.md](../../docs/PLAYGROUND.md)**. **Scripts:** **[scripts/README.md](../../scripts/README.md)**.
